{"Name":"qggnbbfm","Path":"","Id":"qggnbbfm","ActiveCombatantId":null,"RoundCounter":0,"Combatants":[{"Id":"Ancient Black Dragon.cmvf736e","StatBlock":{"Id":"Ancient Black Dragon","Name":"Black Gaping Gutter Dragon","Path":"OTF: Abyss","Source":"OTF / Dark Souls","Type":"Gargantuan dragon, monster manual, chaotic evil","HP":{"Value":367,"Notes":"(21d20+147)"},"AC":{"Value":22,"Notes":"(natural armor)"},"InitiativeModifier":0,"InitiativeAdvantage":false,"Speed":["40 ft.","fly 80 ft.","swim 40 ft."],"Abilities":{"Str":27,"Dex":14,"Con":25,"Int":16,"Wis":15,"Cha":19},"DamageVulnerabilities":[],"DamageResistances":[],"DamageImmunities":["acid"],"ConditionImmunities":[],"Saves":[{"Name":"Dex","Modifier":9},{"Name":"Con","Modifier":14},{"Name":"Wis","Modifier":9},{"Name":"Cha","Modifier":11}],"Skills":[{"Name":"Perception","Modifier":16},{"Name":"Stealth","Modifier":9}],"Senses":["blindsight 60 ft.","darkvision 120 ft."],"Languages":["Common","Draconic"],"Challenge":"21","Traits":[{"Name":"Amphibious","Content":"The dragon can breathe air and water.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Legendary Resistance (3/Day)","Content":"If the dragon fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Magical Tail","Content":"If the gaping dragon takes 40 or more damage to its tail in a single turn, its tail will be cut off. Once this happens, it can no longer use its tail attack.","Usage":""}],"Actions":[{"Name":"Multiattack","Content":"The dragon can use its Frightful Presence. It then makes three attacks: one with its tail and two with its claws OR one stomp attack, one tail attack, and one claw attack. Squirt Bile may replace any one of these attacks.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Bite (Costs a full action)","Content":"Melee Weapon Attack: +15 to hit, reach 30 ft., 30ft x 15ft. Hit: 19 (2d10 + 8) piercing damage plus 9 (2d8) acid damage. A target hit by this attack is swallowed without taking the Claw attack damage detailed by the Swallow action.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Claw","Content":"Melee Weapon Attack: +15 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. Hit: 15 (2d6 + 8) slashing damage.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Tail","Content":"Melee Weapon Attack: +15 to hit, reach 20 ft ., one target. Hit: 17 (2d8 + 8) magical bludgeoning damage.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Frightful Presence","Content":"Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 120 feet of the dragon and aware of it must succeed on a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's saving throw is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to the dragon's Frightful Presence for the next 24 hours.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Acid Breath (Recharge 5-6)","Content":"The dragon exhales acid in a 90-foot line that is 10 feet wide. Each creature in that line must make a DC 22 Dexterity saving throw, taking 67 (15d8) acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Stomp","Content":"Melee Weapon Attack: +15 to hit, reach 5 ft. Hit: 2d6 + 8 bludgeoning damage. Target must make a STR saving throw (DC 23) or be knocked prone.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Acidic Spew (Alt. Acid Breath)","Content":"The gaping dragon regurgitates an acidic, poisonous liquid around itself. Creatures within 20 ft. must succeed on a DC 22 CON saving throw or take 42 (12d6) acid damage, halved on a successful save.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Swallow","Content":"The gaping dragon makes one claw attack against a large or smaller creature it is grappling. If the attack hits, the target takes the claw damage, it is thrown into the gaping dragon's maw, and it is swallowed. While swallowed, the target is blinded and restrained, it has total cover against attacks and other effects outside the gaping dragon, and it takes 21 (6d6) acid damage at the start of each of the gaping dragon's turns.
-- If the gaping dragon takes 30 damage or more on a single turn from a creature inside it, it must succeed on a DC 16 CON saving throw at the end of that turn or regurgitate all swallowed creatures, which fall prone in a space within 10 ft. of the gaping dragon. If the gaping dragon dies, a swallowed creature is no longer restrained by it and can escape from the corpse by using 20 ft. of movement, taking 21 (6d6) acid damage, and exiting prone.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Squirt Bile","Content":"The gaping dragon targets a creature it can see within 120 ft. of it. The target must succeed on a DC 20 DEX saving throw or take 35 (10d6) acid damage and, if flying be grounded. A grounded target may take a turn to remove the slime like bile to re-enable flight.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Warp Creature","Content":"The gaping dragon targets up to 3 creatures it can see within 120 ft. of it. Each target must make a DC 20 CON saving throw. On a successful save, a creature gains advantage for saves against this ability. On a failed save, the target is poisoned, which causes it to also gain 1 level of exhaustion. While poisoned in this way, the target must repeat the saving throw at the start of each of its turns. 3 Successful saves against the poison ends it, and ending the poison removes any levels of exhaustion caused by it. Each failed save causes the target to suffer another level of exhaustion. Once the target reaches 6 levels of exhaustion, it dies and instantly transforms into a living abyssal wretch or Gutter Dragon under the Gaping Dragon's control. The transformation of the body can be undone only by a wish spell.","Usage":""}],"Reactions":[],"LegendaryActions":[{"Name":"Detect","Content":"The dragon makes a Wisdom (Perception) check.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Tail Attack","Content":"The dragon makes a tail attack.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Wing Attack (Costs 2 Actions)","Content":"The dragon beats its wings. Each creature within 15 ft. of the dragon must succeed on a DC 23 Dexterity saving throw or take 15 (2d6 + 8) bludgeoning damage and be knocked prone. The dragon can then fly up to half its flying speed.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Warp (Costs 2 Actions)","Content":"The gaping dragon uses Warp Creature.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Claw Attack","Content":"The gaping dragon makes a claw attack.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Stomp","Content":"The gaping dragon makes a stomp attack.","Usage":""},{"Name":"Squirt Bile","Content":"The gaping dragon makes a squirt bile attack.","Usage":""}],"Description":"Needs modification of Gaping Drapon and Sibriex corruption effects.

An enormous disgusting abonimation that lives deep in the recesses of The Gutter of Aincrad. Its tiny head stands in stark contradiction of the gigantic mouth at its torso, constantly eating everything it runs across. Rows and rows of deadly teeth and poisonous stomach acids leave its prey screaming in pain. Once a majestic dragon, the Gaping Dragon was an early experiment by The Governess to bend dragonkind to her will. With an unending desire for food, it consumed more than its body could hold, its torso burst open, and became an enormous mouth, the ribs sharp teeth and the saliva deadly acid. Still constantly on the prowl for anything to consume in The Gutter of Aincrad, the Gaping Dragon hunts for weak victims. What The Governess was seeking to create when concocting this deformed monstrosity is lost to those with a sane mind. ","Player":"","Version":"1.6.4","ImageURL":""},"MaxHP":367,"CurrentHP":367,"TemporaryHP":0,"Initiative":0,"InitiativeGroup":null,"Alias":"","IndexLabel":1,"Tags":[],"Hidden":false,"InterfaceVersion":"1.6.4","ImageURL":""}],"Version":"1.6.4"}

